my mom pays a man to tell me how much she really loves me deep, down under her facade of irrationality and narcissism. how much i deserve you, how beautiful and intuitive i am. he asks me if he should worry before i leave the office, and i say no. i say no because i don't want someone being paid to care about me. he asked me if i loved myself. what the fuck kind of question is that?

i dont feel as if i deserve to live upon God's wonderful creation, i feel as though i'm not worthy of all of these beautiful people's presence. especially yours, my love. i'm unworthy of even looking in your eyes. but would you please take me anyways? because i'm not even willing to take myself.


<center>take me away from here, bury me somewhere within yourself.

at all.

they're the only reason i would go back to Morro Bay High.

people fucking suck.

those were good mornings.
i miss my stepsister.
i miss my empty room with the chinese mirrors and all matching wicker furniture.
i almost miss the smell.
i don't miss the memories.
i don't want to sleep in that bed again, it holds everything i need to forget.
maybe i'll just get a lock on my door.
fill my little pink bookcase back up.
sit in the sun at the beach with my mexican candy.
walk up the street to Matiana's and let her cook for me and give me 40's hairstyles.
let Alejo finally teach me how to dance.
i'm not shy anymore.
my boyfriend has the hottest butt, ever.
i love rambling.

the fire pits. her. late night burritos. late night walks. sleepovers at kelsey's house. breakfast with three of the best girls the next day. raping bears. screaming. shows. boys kissing. fun drunks and cigarettes. short hair, and spinning. extended elavator rides. tyler and pain killers.

i think it's been something like atleast 6 months.
i think i just want you to wrap me up and lay me in bed again.

from this point on i am going to stop regretting everything that happened.
because i regret a lot of things, but you are not one of them.
and there was a lot of pain, but i wouldnt change a thing.

tonight's weather reminds me a lot like a night in september,
when you kissed me in the driveway and i walked into my room, stunned because i never saw it coming.

i screamed, helpless to myself.

<center>you know it starts here, outside waiting in the cold.
kiss me once in the snow, i swear it never gets old.
but i will promise you i can make it warmer next year.





you know i came here when i needed your soft voice,
i needed to hear something that sounded like an answer.
now i stay here, and everyday i get one.

"Let me tell you something from experience. I will be first to admit I do not have a great deal of experience with relationships, but my experience is solidly convincing of one thing. You will be hurt more than you could ever envision and you will feel better than you could ever imagine possible. After each relationship we want to close up and never let anyone in again. And you would be a fool for doing so. The stories I could tell would make your head spin. I have been broken and hurt to almost cartoony levels (and I am not exaggerating or feeling sorry for myself; there is a typical "lynch mob" reaction when I tell some of the things that have happened) And I wouldn't change a thing. Really, when you get down to it, what do you have to lose? You pour your heart out, you get rejected and hurt, and you grow. And you feel better for getting it all off of your chest. And you are no longer tormented about telling this person. And it is better than being cold and alone. Or they accept. And things work out. The way I see it, There might be a day when I can no longer have such a romantic outlook, when I have worn my heart on my sleeve for the last time, when I must proceed into every relationship with the utmost level of caution. There will be a day when I could never have believed I could have rushed into things like this. And that will be the day that every part of me except my bodily functions dies. Go out and open yourself up and be romantic and fall in love and get hurt while you still have the heart to. There is more beauty in it than you could ever imagine. So cheer up there. Eat Ben and Jerry's from the carton and watch American beauty with all of your friends. It will change your mind about things." sometimes when i feel like total shit i just refer to that and it helps me out a little, so thank you, ben.

it seems as if no one can dream in their own bed anymore.
it seems as if no one can even sleep.

fuck dreams that are probably true.

ben and jesse pulled up the the curb, i saw them and screamed. my boyfriend had left for band practice before i got there. ben has intense veins. mike has a cool belt. yep. we love the tobacco. ben. he made me happy yesterday.

i took my arms, left on top. they were back, somewhere in between broken chords and simple strums, they flooded back. 

memories; i can't let go. i need to, but i wont. i wont ever let something like that happen to me again. i wont ever let myself be taken advantage of as i lay blind. 
or will i? have i?

sleep is a sickness, it travels from your feet, to your ankles; your knees and hips go next. the steady need for rest takes you over and you shake a bit, until the hunger consumes you and you go to bed. but not me when i was in that house.

i struggled against it with every shallow breath. i would be awake for hours, hearing the steady waves outside my door and waiting for what i knew would eventually come. i walked the halls, i stalked the halls, trying madly to stay awake until __ went away, only to pass out onto the carpeted corridor and get yelled at the next day. 

sleepwalking? 
no, i don't think that's what you would call it.





you give, and you take away.
and you think you have something pure?!

ugh, i'm so sick of it you have no idea.

and the way you try to pull it off?
it makes it about 1,846,223,418 times worse.

here i am, my feet are wet.
a boy i havent spoken with since last year says hello,
i smile.
this place suffocates,
come breathe into me a bit.

You're Alice's Adventures in Wonderland!
by Lewis Carroll
After stumbling down the wrong turn in life, you've had your mind opened to a number of strange and curious things. As life grows curiouser and curiouser, you have to ask yourself what's real and what's the picture of illusion. Little is coming to your aid in discerning fantasy from fact, but the line between them is so blurry that it's starting not to matter. Be careful around rabbit holes and those who smile to much, and just avoid hat shops altogether.
